<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="841" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">311.6124/15a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Commissioner at Helsingfors</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Haynes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-07T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 7,
                                        1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Situation is developing in Latvia in such a way as to make it unlikely
                            that deported aliens can be transferred to Bolshevik Russia through
                            Libau. Telegraph urgently whether it would be possible to arrange for
                            their transfer through Hangö. They number 249. The ship would reach
                            Hangö probably January 12. This Government would, of course, bear all
                            expense connected with the transfer.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
